<detall><id label=""><![CDATA[96115]]></id><title label="Titol"><![CDATA[Experience the theatre with your family]]></title><excerpt label="Resum"><![CDATA[The Teatre Poliorama, the Romea and the CCCB are presenting plays over the weekends aimed at children aged 0 to 12.]]></excerpt><content label="Contingut"><![CDATA[<p>The Teatre Poliorama and the Romea will be presenting two new shows over the coming months as part of the <em>Viu el Teatre!</em><br />
cycle.<br />
The Poliorama is presenting the play <em>Les princeses també es tiren pets</em> [Princesses fart too] and the Romea, the show <em>Perduts a la Viquipèdia</em> [Lost in Wikipedia]. The former tells the story of the Queen of Mirrors who wishes to find the book that contains all the secrets of the world&#8217;s most famous princesses. It&#8217;s at this point that a madcap adventure starts, which ends on a note that shows perfection neither exists nor is needed<strong>. </strong><br />
As for <em>Perduts a la Viquipèdia</em>, this is a work that brings together family theatre and science, starring children and adults, which helps us to see the world from a scientific perspective.</p>
